      "content": "A super low inventory turnover ratio usually means you have too much extra stuff just sitting in the back, but it's often caused by a few specific reasons. For instance, you might have bought too many trendy items that nobody is wearing, or perhaps your marketing is just not reaching the right customers to sell them. It could also be that you're holding onto items that are slightly out of style, or maybe you simply forgot to restock your shelves because you were too busy with other tasks. In any case, it's a clear sign that your current stock is not moving fast enough to cover your costs.",
