      "content": "To determine if this is a temporary slow period or a serious problem, you should look at your inventory turnover ratio over the last few months and compare it to your historical averages. If the ratio has been consistently low for several quarters, it indicates a serious problem with your stock levels rather than a fleeting seasonal dip. Additionally, check if your sales velocity has dropped significantly compared to your peak seasons; if it's been flat or declining, it suggests a deeper issue with your product mix or marketing strategy. You might also consider running a quick analysis of your best-selling items to see if the slow-moving summer stock is actually cannibalizing your sales or if it's just sitting there unused.",
